  "id": "vectors-CN",
  "title": "China \u2014 field boundary predictions",
  "description": "Field-boundary predictions for China, split into 69 admin-subdivision partitions. Each polygon carries a `confidence` value (0\u2013100): the modeled PRUE confidence sampled at the field's point-on-surface from the 500 m confidence COG (the `predictions/confidence` collection), rescaled `raw / 0.578178 * 100` and clamped to 100 (cells with no data become null). 0.578178 is treated as 100%, matching the FTW inference app; this centroid sample is the closest single value to the app's `confidence_mean`. Recommended default reliability filter: confidence >= 69 (raw 0.4). Confidence reflects cell-level model reliability, not individual-polygon geometric accuracy. Generated by `add_confidence.py` (+ `process_partition.sh`, `run_rails.sh`, `make_pmtiles.py`): https://github.com/fieldsoftheworld/ftw-portolan/blob/main/scripts/add_confidence.py",
